<table align=right class=spellbox><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td align=right nowrap>Mana Cost:</td><td nowrap><font class=spell>10</font></td></tr><tr><td align=right nowrap>Cast Time:</td><td nowrap><font class=spell>2.5</font></td></tr><tr><td align=right nowrap>Resist:</td><td nowrap><font class=spell>Unresistable</font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><ul>Description: <font class=spell>This spell creates an invisible field of energy around you, raising hit points, armor class and magic resistance.<br><ul>
<LI>Increase Max Hitpoints by 6 (L1) to 10 (L5)<LI>Increase AC by 3 (L1) to 4 (L5)</ul></font><br>Whizbang's Notes: <ul><font class=spell>This is the first of a line of spells shared by all casters (as opposed to healers). As it is the cheapest and easiest means we have of protecting ourselves, unless a better alternative is available in the form of a spell cast by someone else, there's no reason not to use these spells. And while the benefits granted by Minor Shielding are, well, minor, always keeping it maintained keeps the Abjuration spell skill up, which enables one to cast, say, Shield of the Magi later on without worrying about whether the spell will fizzle. (Well, much.)</font></ul><br>Graffe's Old Notes: <ul><font class=spell>This can only be cast upon yourself and adds armor class and hit points. Not much added, but invaluable for a wizard at this level where melee is part of the equation for battles.</font></ul></ul>
